 * DotNet Bookstore — In-Class ASP.NET Core MVC Project
 * Course: COMP2084 | Georgian College | Summer 2026
 * Instructor: Dario Hesami
 * ============================================================================
 *
 * FILE:    Views/_ViewStart.cshtml
 * PURPOSE: Runs BEFORE every Razor view is rendered (hence "_ViewStart").
 *          Its only job here is to set the default layout template that all
 *          views should be wrapped in.
 *
 * KEY CONCEPTS FOR STUDENTS:
 *  1. _ViewStart.cshtml  — an implicit hook that runs at the start of every
 *                          view in this folder and all sub-folders. It is
 *                          discovered and executed automatically by the Razor
 *                          view engine — you never call it directly.
 *  2. Layout property    — setting Layout = "_Layout" tells every view to wrap
 *                          itself inside Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml by default.
 *                          An individual view can override this with:
 *                            @{ Layout = "AnotherLayout"; }  // use a different layout
 *                            @{ Layout = null; }             // no layout (raw HTML only)
 *  3. Why use a layout?  — defining the layout here once means every new view
 *                          you add will automatically have the navbar, footer,
 *                          and script tags — without repeating them.
 * ============================================================================
 *@

@{
    @* Apply the shared layout to every view in the application.
       The path is relative — Razor looks in Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml. *@
    Layout = "_Layout";
}
